HEADWORD: Aration
<hw>A*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aratio</ets>, fr. <ets>arare</ets> to plow.]</ety> <def>Plowing;
tillage.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lands are said to be in a state of <qex>aration</qex> when they
are under tillage.</q> <rj><qau>Brande.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aratory</ent>⟦br⟧
